{
  "text": "Initially, laboratory studies of tornado-like vortices were performed to improve our understanding of tornado dynamics (e.g., Ward 1972; [CITATION_1] . These studies have shown that a key parameter pertaining to vortex structure is swirl ratio. Swirl ratio has traditionally been defined as",
